main.WhyWriteCompiler

Here are some reasons why you would want to write a compiler.

## Learn how programs execute

By writing a compiler, you gain insight into how programs are actually
executed.

You no longer have to live with the feeling that programming is writing code in
Java or in Python. If you know how to make your own language execute on a
computer, you no longer need to choose any of the existing languages.

## Increase problem solving techniques

Introducing a new language to solve a particular program is a powerful
technique. If you know how to implement a compiler, you are more likely to use
this technique.

